      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Create an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.networkingdriverkit/documentation/NetworkingDriverKit/IOUserNetworkPacketBufferPool",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " during the initial setup of your driver and use it to store the packets that your driver transmits or receives. Every driver must have a packet buffer pool large enough to hold all of the packets in its transmit and receive queues. You allocate this pool early in the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/kernel/ioservice/3180710-start",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method of your ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.networkingdriverkit/documentation/NetworkingDriverKit/IOUserNetworkEthernet",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " service, and you deallocate that pool only after your service stops.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
